        deviceFilterHelper - Helper for creating the device filter string. This helper can be used instead of setting device filter directly. This allows the campaign filter to be created in a way which is similar to the device listing filter.
        autostopReason - Text description of why a campaign failed to start or why a campaign stopped.
        createdAt - The time the update campaign was created.
        description - An optional description of the campaign.
        deviceFilter - The filter for the devices the campaign is targeting at.
        finished - The campaign finish timestamp.
        id - The campaign ID.
        name - The campaign name.
        phase - The current phase of the campaign.
        rootManifestId - value.
        rootManifestUrl - value.
        startedAt - value.
        updatedAt - The time the object was updated.
        when - The scheduled start time for the campaign. The campaign will start within 1 minute when then start time has elapsed.

    • Method Detail

      • getDeviceFiltersHelper

        public Filters getDeviceFiltersHelper()
        Gets the device filter (AbstractUpdateCampaign.getDeviceFilter()) defined as a generic Filters.

        This helper can be used instead of getting device filter directly (AbstractUpdateCampaign.getDeviceFilter()) as a string. This allows the campaign filter to be seen and defined in a way which is similar to the device listing filter.

        Returns:
        deviceFilterHelper

      • setDeviceFiltersHelper

        public void setDeviceFiltersHelper(Filters deviceFilter)
        Sets the device filter (AbstractUpdateCampaign.setDeviceFilter(String)) using a generic Filters object defined within ListOptions.

        This helper can be used instead of setting device filter directly. This allows the campaign filter to be created in a way which is similar to the device listing filter. It is hence possible to define the filter using the DeviceListOptions helpers and then pass it to a campaign using FilterOptions.getFilter().

        Parameters:
        deviceFilter - Helper for creating the device filter string. This helper can be used instead of setting device filter directly. This allows the campaign filter to be created in a way which is similar to the device listing filter.
